1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:37,960
=Episode 6=

3
00:01:42,440 --> 00:01:42,800
Ming,

4
00:01:43,080 --> 00:01:44,160
how about you deposit that money
with me?

5
00:01:44,479 --> 00:01:45,160
What money?

6
00:01:45,720 --> 00:01:46,960
Do not try to hide it from me.

7
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,279
The news is already everywhere.

8
00:01:48,399 --> 00:01:49,160
Let's talk about it inside.

9
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:57,999
So,

10
00:01:58,279 --> 00:01:59,320
about the money...

11
00:01:59,639 --> 00:02:00,479
How did you know?

12
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,359
You won such a huge lottery prize.

13
00:02:02,399 --> 00:02:03,160
Who would not know?

14
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,440
When you claimed the prize,

15
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:05,359
you did wear a full-head mask.

16
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,160
But that outfit of yours...

17
00:02:07,240 --> 00:02:08,239
You have worn it for years.

18
00:02:08,239 --> 00:02:09,759
I recognized you at once.

19
00:02:13,959 --> 00:02:15,280
So, everyone recognized him.

20
00:02:15,359 --> 00:02:15,799
Is that so?

21
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,320
Didn't you donate four million?

22
00:02:19,519 --> 00:02:21,280
You won 130 million!

23
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:22,919
Ming, Yitong,

24
00:02:23,239 --> 00:02:25,040
you guys are truly blessed.

25
00:02:25,239 --> 00:02:26,759
As the old saying goes,

26
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,560
wealth should stay within the family.

27
00:02:28,679 --> 00:02:29,759
In any case, this money

28
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:30,959
will have to be deposited somewhere.

29
00:02:31,239 --> 00:02:31,799
Why not

30
00:02:32,079 --> 00:02:32,600
deposit it with me?

31
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:33,359
I will secure

32
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:34,479
the best terms for you both.

33
00:02:34,959 --> 00:02:36,239
I will handle it personally.

34
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:37,440
After all, we're...

35
00:02:37,440 --> 00:02:37,919
Kneel.

36
00:02:43,160 --> 00:02:43,639
Ming,

37
00:02:44,759 --> 00:02:46,120
considering our relationship,

38
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,040
is this really necessary?

39
00:02:51,160 --> 00:02:51,560
Get out.

40
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:52,600
- Out.
- Ming.

41
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:54,239
Ming, listen to me.

42
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:54,840
- I...
- Get out.

43
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,040
I know you are still angry with me.

44
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:56,440
Out.

45
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,679
But we are family.

46
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:59,320
Blood is thicker than water, Ming.

47
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:00,160
But this time,

48
00:03:00,239 --> 00:03:01,359
you really have to help me.

49
00:03:01,679 --> 00:03:02,079
Please, Ming.

50
00:03:05,239 --> 00:03:05,679
Dad.

51
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:07,120
Impressive.

52
00:03:16,519 --> 00:03:16,919
Li.

53
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:18,720
That jackpot of over 100 million...

54
00:03:18,959 --> 00:03:20,079
Was it really sold here?

55
00:03:20,199 --> 00:03:20,919
Of course, it was.

56
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,840
The Lottery Center called to notify us.

57
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,519
The winning ticket came from our shop.

58
00:03:25,079 --> 00:03:25,679
Good heavens!

59
00:03:25,919 --> 00:03:26,160
Wait.

60
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:27,600
Such huge news broke last night.

61
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:28,400
Did you not hear about it?

62
00:03:28,679 --> 00:03:29,239
Over there.

63
00:03:29,359 --> 00:03:30,519
It is playing on a loop.

64
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:31,160
Check it out.

65
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,440
Honey, raise your side a little.

66
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,040
Okay, okay.

67
00:03:33,239 --> 00:03:35,160
Over 100 million! My goodness!

68
00:03:35,359 --> 00:03:36,359
How can someone be so lucky?

69
00:03:36,479 --> 00:03:37,720
Why do we never have such luck?

70
00:03:38,239 --> 00:03:39,359
There are only a few people

71
00:03:39,479 --> 00:03:40,840
who buy lottery tickets around here.

72
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:41,919
Who do you think it is?

73
00:03:42,359 --> 00:03:43,560
Li, tell us. Tell us.

74
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:44,280
I cannot say.

75
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:45,759
Come on, just tell us.

76
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:47,280
I do not know either.

77
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:50,359
It is a man.

78
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:50,720
You...

79
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:51,400
Are you blind?

80
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,199
I...

81
00:03:52,199 --> 00:03:52,799
I am your father.

82
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,199
If I weren't so busy today,

83
00:03:57,199 --> 00:03:57,880
you'd be dead.

84
00:04:00,199 --> 00:04:00,639
It is a man.

85
00:04:00,799 --> 00:04:01,639
Not necessarily.

86
00:04:01,799 --> 00:04:02,679
That person wore a mask.

87
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:03,560
Look.

88
00:04:03,799 --> 00:04:05,000
What kind of mask is that?

89
00:04:05,919 --> 00:04:06,880
(My customer won 130 million yuan!)
Isn't that a fish?

90
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:08,359
(My customer won 130 million yuan!)
That fish looks

91
00:04:08,799 --> 00:04:09,560
rather ugly.

92
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,280
Listen to yourself.

93
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,320
Ugly or not, it's still a rich fish.

94
00:04:13,519 --> 00:04:15,079
Fish...
[*Fish is pronounced as yu in Chinese]

95
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,439
Yu Ming!

96
00:04:16,919 --> 00:04:17,720
It's him!

97
00:04:17,799 --> 00:04:18,520
Unbelievable!

98
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:20,119
It is him! He lives upstairs from me!

99
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,919
He used to have feelings for me.

100
00:04:21,999 --> 00:04:23,200
I always knew that fellow

101
00:04:23,239 --> 00:04:24,400
was destined for good fortune.

102
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,679
I bought the ticket with him back then.

103
00:04:27,239 --> 00:04:28,439
Back then, back then...

104
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:29,600
I bought one back then, too!

105
00:04:30,319 --> 00:04:31,439
- Unbelievable.
- I lost a fortune.

106
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:33,640
Over 100 million.
This is no small matter!

107
00:04:33,799 --> 00:04:34,400
Yitong.

108
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,040
This serum was recommended

109
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:36,919
by a colleague of mine.

110
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,040
Apart from being a little expensive,

111
00:04:38,160 --> 00:04:39,479
it has no other flaws.

112
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,760
One box is nearly 900 yuan.

113
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,200
Makes your skin fair and firm.

114
00:04:44,080 --> 00:04:44,919
I bought two

115
00:04:44,919 --> 00:04:45,999
and had them sent to your place.

116
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,879
Also, the light therapy device

117
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,080
and the mist hydrator.

118
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:49,919
Very high-tech.

119
00:04:50,359 --> 00:04:51,040
Once your skin is hydrated,

120
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,119
you can move on to firming.

121
00:04:52,359 --> 00:04:53,319
At our age,

122
00:04:53,520 --> 00:04:54,239
our faces cannot sag.

123
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:55,319
It needs lifting.

124
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,200
We have to be willing

125
00:04:56,200 --> 00:04:57,439
to invest in our faces.

126
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,640
Before this,

127
00:04:58,760 --> 00:04:59,559
you simply never learned

128
00:04:59,679 --> 00:05:00,640
to spend money on yourself.

129
00:05:00,799 --> 00:05:01,919
So, Qian Zihan's mother's voice

130
00:05:01,919 --> 00:05:02,960
can actually sound sweet.

131
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:05,919
How does it sound
so much like an insult?

132
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,720
You recognized her

133
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,319
just by

134
00:05:08,319 --> 00:05:09,479
listening?

135
00:05:12,359 --> 00:05:13,400
Hold on to your backpack.

136
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:17,080
Focus in class and keep out of trouble.

137
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,600
Money really is powerful.

138
00:05:24,999 --> 00:05:26,720
Makes voices sound good
and people look good.

139
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:27,559
Let's go.

140
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:36,040
Stack them properly.

141
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,760
We were right to return the goods.

142
00:05:39,919 --> 00:05:41,119
The money
looks much better arranged neatly.

143
00:05:43,520 --> 00:05:45,080
Neat, yes.

144
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:46,960
But even with that much money,

145
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,319
we cannot spend recklessly.

146
00:05:48,359 --> 00:05:49,600
Nor should we waste it.

147
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,720
And returning items is a loss of face.

148
00:05:51,799 --> 00:05:52,919
Listen. Upgrading our lifestyle

149
00:05:52,919 --> 00:05:54,080
has to be gradual.

150
00:05:54,559 --> 00:05:55,280
If we suddenly

151
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:56,400
spend a huge amount,

152
00:05:56,479 --> 00:05:57,600
change our clothes and accessories,

153
00:05:57,600 --> 00:05:58,640
how would we explain it

154
00:05:58,640 --> 00:05:59,119
when people ask?

155
00:05:59,239 --> 00:06:00,119
We won the lottery.

156
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,119
They have already given us

157
00:06:01,119 --> 00:06:01,999
the perfect excuse.

158
00:06:01,999 --> 00:06:03,239
We can simply play along.

159
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:04,799
Just use the excuse they gave us.

160
00:06:04,799 --> 00:06:05,720
No, not like that.

161
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,439
About the lottery,

162
00:06:06,439 --> 00:06:07,600
we must not say it ourselves.

163
00:06:07,679 --> 00:06:08,720
That would make it a lie.

164
00:06:08,799 --> 00:06:09,479
If others say it,

165
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:10,799
we just laugh it off.

166
00:06:10,960 --> 00:06:11,679
When someone asks,

167
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,559
"Where did the money come from?"

168
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,239
We just laugh it off,

169
00:06:13,879 --> 00:06:15,080
smile,

170
00:06:15,080 --> 00:06:15,840
and let it pass.

171
00:06:15,919 --> 00:06:16,520
Understand?

172
00:06:16,999 --> 00:06:17,879
Exactly.

173
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,319
You have a better grasp of the law.

174
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:20,380
(Hong Jinkui)

175
00:06:20,439 --> 00:06:22,200
(Hong Jinkui)
He has called dozens of times.

176
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,040
(Hong Jinkui)
Should I answer?

177
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,200
Answer it. See what he wants.

178
00:06:27,520 --> 00:06:28,160
Ming.

179
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,479
Now that you are rich,

180
00:06:30,559 --> 00:06:31,520
you really are a different man.

181
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:33,200
Even meeting you is difficult now.

182
00:06:35,119 --> 00:06:35,760
Haha.

183
00:06:39,799 --> 00:06:40,679
Here is the thing.

184
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:42,040
I have thought it over.

185
00:06:42,119 --> 00:06:42,720
I was the one

186
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,879
who helped you get your villa.

187
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:45,080
So, you shouldn't
pay the property management fees.

188
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:45,879
I will cover them.

189
00:06:45,999 --> 00:06:46,760
As your bro,

190
00:06:46,799 --> 00:06:48,439
I cannot let my own brother lose out.

191
00:06:48,439 --> 00:06:48,799
Right?

192
00:06:49,479 --> 00:06:50,119
Haha.

193
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,359
Don't just laugh.

194
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,520
I know, deep down,

195
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:55,200
you're upset with me.

196
00:06:55,239 --> 00:06:56,280
Back then, I was

197
00:06:56,400 --> 00:06:57,200
short on cash myself.

198
00:06:57,239 --> 00:06:57,879
I had to pull the money together

199
00:06:57,879 --> 00:06:58,960
from everywhere.

200
00:06:59,040 --> 00:06:59,919
Doesn't that show sincerity?

201
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:00,479
How about this?

202
00:07:00,479 --> 00:07:01,200
Let us put this behind us.

203
00:07:01,359 --> 00:07:02,280
I am almost at the property office.

204
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:03,439
After I pay,

205
00:07:03,479 --> 00:07:04,720
could we find somewhere
to sit and chat

206
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:05,200
for a bit?

207
00:07:07,119 --> 00:07:07,679
Haha...

208
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:09,679
Pay the property management fees first.

209
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:10,319
Then we will see.

210
00:07:11,919 --> 00:07:12,679
All right.

211
00:07:12,679 --> 00:07:13,439
Of course, Yitong.

212
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,200
Haha?

213
00:07:19,359 --> 00:07:20,439
What was that for?

214
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:21,280
Haha?

215
00:07:21,319 --> 00:07:22,280
Why laugh like that?

216
00:07:22,559 --> 00:07:23,919
You told me to laugh it off.

217
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,040
He offered
to pay the property management fees.

218
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:26,119
You should have heard him out

219
00:07:26,119 --> 00:07:26,559
before deciding

220
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:27,559
whether to laugh it off.

221
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:28,160
No, I...

222
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:28,799
With you here,

223
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,160
I get nervous.

224
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,080
I cannot think straight.

225
00:07:31,119 --> 00:07:32,600
What should I do, die? Disappear?

226
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,400
Why say something so unlucky?

227
00:07:34,479 --> 00:07:35,760
Stop laughing at random.

228
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:47,799
Mr. Hong.

229
00:07:48,119 --> 00:07:50,040
For Unit 505, the water, electricity,

230
00:07:50,400 --> 00:07:51,640
and property management fees
total 120,000.

231
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:53,239
Everything has been paid.

232
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:55,080
Please keep the receipt.

233
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,160
The payment went through, right?

234
00:07:56,919 --> 00:07:58,400
So starting today,

235
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,760
for Unit 505, trucks carrying

236
00:07:59,799 --> 00:08:01,359
construction waste and furniture

237
00:08:01,359 --> 00:08:02,960
can come and go as needed,

238
00:08:02,999 --> 00:08:03,679
with no obstruction?

239
00:08:03,799 --> 00:08:04,600
No obstruction.

240
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:05,799
Listen carefully.

241
00:08:06,439 --> 00:08:07,999
No more giving people a hard time.

242
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:09,239
My brother's family
is renovating their home.

243
00:08:09,239 --> 00:08:10,559
Make it easy for them.

244
00:08:10,679 --> 00:08:11,200
Otherwise,

245
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,359
I will file a complaint.

246
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:13,319
I will report every one of you.

247
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,520
Take care, Mr. Hong.

248
00:08:17,720 --> 00:08:18,679
Who would have thought?

249
00:08:19,239 --> 00:08:20,720
Mr. Yu

250
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:22,319
has some real influence.

251
00:08:22,799 --> 00:08:24,760
He made that guy pay 120,000.

252
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:26,840
Quite a figure.

253
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:38,000
♪Work hard and make money♪

254
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,400
♪I want to get rich♪

255
00:08:39,880 --> 00:08:41,640
(Sun Meimei, Hong Jinkui)
♪A villa by the sea♪

256
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,040
(Sun Meimei, Hong Jinkui)
♪Seafood every day♪

257
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:45,360
♪Fancy cars, pick what I want.♪

258
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:49,719
Ming, this is Hong, your bro.

259
00:08:49,799 --> 00:08:50,520
Yitong.

260
00:08:50,679 --> 00:08:51,480
I noticed

261
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:53,240
you looked pale the other day.

262
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:53,839
Here's the thing.

263
00:08:53,839 --> 00:08:54,559
Let me update you.

264
00:08:54,719 --> 00:08:55,799
For Unit 505,

265
00:08:55,799 --> 00:08:56,919
the 120,000 in property management fees,

266
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,599
I paid it for you.

267
00:08:57,599 --> 00:08:58,240
I made you

268
00:08:58,319 --> 00:09:00,480
angelica, ginger, and lamb soup.

269
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:01,199
And also,

270
00:09:01,240 --> 00:09:02,120
in a little while,

271
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,079
I will bring you the invoice.

272
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:03,640
Where are you?

273
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:04,599
Where are you?

274
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:06,280
I will bring it over, all right?

275
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:06,719
Fine.

276
00:09:06,919 --> 00:09:08,199
Make the soup if you want.

277
00:09:08,199 --> 00:09:08,880
Just leave it at home.

278
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:09,880
Send the invoice to the shop first.

279
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,079
I will send you the location.

280
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,599
Drink more. Have some more.

281
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:29,000
Yitong.

282
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:31,040
If you want to have a child,

283
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,839
you must take good care of your body.

284
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:33,880
Do you like the soup?

285
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,360
I can make it for you every day.

286
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:36,919
After all,

287
00:09:36,959 --> 00:09:38,120
I am already retired.

288
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,559
I have plenty of time.

289
00:09:39,919 --> 00:09:40,760
Let me tell you.

290
